\title{Datalog Fixpoint}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{trit}{0}

\meta{description}{Datalog bottom-up fixpoint iteration for recursive queries}

\subtree{
\title{Datalog Fixpoint Skill}
\p{Bottom-up fixpoint iteration for recursive Datalog queries without explicit recursion.}

\subtree{
\title{Core Concept}
\p{Datalog computes fixpoints via iterative saturation:}

\pre{\startverb
T^0(∅) → T^1 → T^2 → ... → T^ω (fixpoint)
\stopverb}

\p{Where T is the immediate consequence operator.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Cat# Integration}
\p{Fixpoint computation maps to Cat# via coalgebraic semantics:}

\pre{\startverb
Trit: 0 (ERGODIC - iterative bridge)
Home: Prof (profunctors/bimodules)
Poly Op: ⊗ (parallel saturation)
Kan Role: Adj (Kleisli adjunction)
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Naturality}
\p{Datalog fixpoint iteration is inherently ERGODIC:}

\ul{
\li{Each iteration step is a natural transformation}
\li{Convergence = reaching the terminal coalgebra}
\li{The fixpoint IS the bicomodule equilibrium}
}
}
}
}